[SN]TITLE[SN]
Four Scots to run at World Indoor Championships

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Four Scots have been named in the Great Britain squad for the World Indoor Championships in Portland, Oregon, later this month.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
2014 Commonwealth Games and European Championships silver medallist Lynsey Sharp has been selected for the 800m in the event running from 17-20 March.
Steph Twell and Josephine Moultrie both go in the 3000m.
Chris O'Hare, who won bronze in the European Indoor Championships last year, will compete over 1500m.
